---
description: Visual and frontend quality rules for WebOS sites
alwaysApply: true
---

- The site should feel premium, warm, spacious, and professional.
- Use design tokens for typography, spacing, colors, and radius.
- Avoid generic AI-site aesthetics: purple gradients, bubbly cards, centered-everything layouts, icon-in-circle feature grids.
- Default to left-aligned content outside of hero moments.
- Build reusable section patterns that can serve future business sites.
- Keep motion subtle and purposeful.
- Optimize for clean editing and maintainable components.
